{% extends "base.html.twig" %}

{% block title %}{{ parent() }} Tour de France 2022{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <div class="container mt-5">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-12 text-center">
                <h1>Tour de France 2022</h1>
                <p class="lead">Welcome to the official presentation page of the Tour de France 2022.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row mt-4">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <h2>About the Event</h2>
                <p>The Tour de France is an annual men's multiple stage bicycle race primarily held in France, while
                    also occasionally passing through nearby countries. The race was first organized in 1903 to increase
                    sales for the newspaper L'Auto and is currently run by the Amaury Sport Organisation.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <img src="images/imagebase.avif" class="img-fluid" alt="Tour de France 2022">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row mt-4">
            <div class="col-12">
                <h2>Stages</h2>
                <p>The 2022 edition of the Tour de France will feature 21 stages, covering a total distance of
                    approximately 3,500 kilometers. The stages include a mix of flat, hilly, and mountainous terrain, as
                    well as individual time trials.</p>
                <ul>
                    {% for etape in etapes %}
                        <li>Stage from {{ etape.ville_dep }} to {{ etape.ville_arr }} ({{ etape.distance }} km)</li>
                    {% endfor %}
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row mt-4">
            <div class="col-12">
                <h2>Teams and Riders</h2>
                <p>The Tour de France 2022 will feature 22 teams, each consisting of 8 riders. Some of the top teams and
                    riders to watch out for include:</p>
                <table class="table table-striped">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Team Name</th>
                            <th>Riders</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        {% for equipe in equipes %}
                            <tr>
                                <td>{{ equipe.nom_equipe }}</td>
                                <td>{{ equipe.coureurs }}</td>
                            </tr>
                        {% endfor %}
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endblock %}